Anemone acutiloba is a herbaceous perennial plant native to North America. 
Its flowers have dark purple sepals that contrast with the yellow stamen. 
The plant can reach a height of up to 2 feet. 
Its leaves are deeply divided and have a toothed margin. 
It grows in moist areas such as swamps, bogs, and streambanks. 
The Anemone acutiloba is commonly used in native plant gardens due to its unique appearances and native habitat. 
It is also used in traditional medicine to treat various ailments such as rheumatism and sore eyes.
